<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029760"><name>1VD-FTV ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0309414"><name>ECD SYSTEM(w/o EGR System)</name><para id="RM10000000136JN" category="J"><dtccode/><dtcname>Pre-heating Control Circuit</dtcname><subpara id="RM10000000136JN_01" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The glow plug is mounted inside the engine combustion chamber. To ensure efficient engine starting with a cold engine, the ECM calculates a time interval of the current that needs to flow through the glow plug depending on the starting engine coolant temperature when the ignition switch is turned to ON. The ECM then turns on the glow plug relay and permits the current to flow through the glow plug based on the ECM&apos;s calculated time. The glow plug relay is then heated, and enhances fuel combustion with a cold engine.</ptxt><ptxt>This DTC will be set if the glow plug or the circuit is open.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="A154593E07" width="7.168479331in" height="3.812598425in"/></figure><atten4><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>These troubleshooting procedures are for: 1) difficult engine starting in cold weather, and 2) difficulty driving / vehicle malfunctions in cold weather immediately after engine is started.</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>After the engine is started, the ECM performs an &quot;after-glow&quot; for a certain period of time. In proportion to the actual engine coolant temperature, the time period varies. The after-glow reduces diesel engine knocking, white smoke emissions and engine noises when the engine is cold.</ptxt></item></list1></atten4><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="A303110E12" width="7.168479331in" height="4.825319882in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM10000000136JN_02" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="A335944E02" width="7.168479331in" height="7.863484252in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM10000000136JN_03" category="10"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten3><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Inspect the fuses for circuits related to this system before performing the following inspection procedure.</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>After replacing the ECM, the new ECM needs registration (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM10000000136W1"/></mlink>) and initialization (See page <mlink><xref label="Seep00002" term-id-from="003" href="RM10000000136K9"/></mlink>).</ptxt></item></list1></atten3></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM10000000136JN_05" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM10000000136JN_05_0001" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK ECM TERMINAL VOLTAGE (GREL TERMINAL)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Remove the GLOW1 and GLOW2 relays from the engine room relay block assembly.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A225237C01" width="3.434793307in" height="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>Engine Room Relay Block Assembly</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>GLOW 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*3</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>GLOW 2</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the voltage according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard voltage</title><table><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Switch Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>GLOW 1 relay holder 2 - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Ignition switch ON</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>11 to 14 V</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>GLOW 2 relay holder 2 - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Ignition switch ON</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>11 to 14 V</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-1" childid="RM10000000136JN_05_0002"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-3"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-3" childid="RM10000000136JN_05_0011"/></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136JN_05_0002" cellposition="2-1"><testtitle>INSPECT GLOW RELAY (NO. 1 OR NO. 2)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Inspect the glow relay.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001" href="RM100000000FPLC"/></mlink></ptxt></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="2-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="4-1" childid="RM10000000136JN_05_0004"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="2-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-2"><actiontitle>REPLACE GLOW RELAY (NO. 1 OR NO. 2)</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136JN_05_0004" cellposition="4-1"><testtitle>INSPECT GLOW PLUG ASSEMBLY (RESISTANCE)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the glow plug connector.</ptxt><figure type="1" translate="C"><graphic graphicname="A163041C01" width="3.434793307in" height="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>Screw Grommet</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance</title><table><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Glow plug terminal - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>20°C (68°F)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Approximately 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec><atten4><ptxt>If any of the glow plugs has an open circuit, the engine power will be insufficient only when the engine is cold.</ptxt></atten4><atten3><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Exercise extreme care not to damage the glow plug pipes. Damaging them could cause an open circuit, or shorten the life of the glow plugs.</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Keep the glow plugs free of oil and fuel while cleaning.</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Wipe any oil off of the terminal and Bakelite washer with a clean, dry cloth during inspection.</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>Do not apply more than 11 V to the glow plugs as it may cause an open circuit.</ptxt></item></list1></atten3></test1><test1><ptxt>Reconnect the glow plug connector.</ptxt></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="4-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="6-1" childid="RM10000000136JN_05_0006"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="4-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="5-2"><actiontitle>REPLACE GLOW PLUG ASSEMBLY</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="002" href="RM10000000103Z8"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136JN_05_0006" cellposition="6-1"><testtitle>CHECK GLOW PLUG ASSEMBLY (INSTALLATION)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Check the glow plug installation.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="002" href="RM10000000103Z9"/></mlink></ptxt><spec type="other"><title>OK</title><specitem><ptxt>Glow plugs are installed securely.</ptxt></specitem></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="6-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="8-1" childid="RM10000000136JN_05_0008"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="6-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="7-2"><actiontitle>TIGHTEN GLOW PLUG</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136JN_05_0008" cellposition="8-1"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (GLOW RELAY - GLOW PLUG - BATTERY AND BODY GROUND)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Remove the GLOW1 and GLOW2 relays from the engine room relay block assembly.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the glow plug connectors.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the cable from the negative (-) battery terminal.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the cable from the positive (+) battery terminal.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance No. 1</title><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.37in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.37in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.34in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>GLOW 1 relay terminal 3 - C45-1</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>GLOW 1 relay terminal 5 - Positive (+) battery terminal cable</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>GLOW 1 relay terminal 2 - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance No. 2</title><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.37in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.37in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.34in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>GLOW 2 relay terminal 3 - C62-1</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>GLOW 2 relay terminal 5 - Positive (+) battery terminal cable</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>GLOW 2 relay terminal 2 - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="8-1"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="9-1"><actiontitle>CHECK FOR INTERMITTENT PROBLEMS</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM10000000136K6"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="8-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="9-2"><actiontitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM10000000136JN_05_0011" cellposition="2-3"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (GLOW RELAY - ECM AND BODY GROUND)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Remove the GLOW1 and GLOW2 relays from the engine room R/B assembly.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the ECM connector.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance</title><table pgwide="1"><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.37in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="2.37in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="2.34in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>GLOW 1 relay terminal 2 - C39-63 (GREL)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>GLOW 2 relay terminal 2 - C39-62 (GRL2)</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>GLOW 1 relay terminal 2 or C39-63 (GREL) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>GLOW 2 relay terminal 2 or C39-62 (GRL2) - Body ground</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="2-3"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-3"><actiontitle>REPLACE ECM</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000013IGX"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="2-4"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-4"><actiontitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp></subpara></para></ttl></section></servcat></pub></tmc-service-paragraph>